headline: Stronger Q4 Results and Higher Dividend Might Change The Case For Investing In Phillips 66 (PSX)
summary: In early February 2026, Phillips 66 reported fourth-quarter 2025 revenue of US$36,333 million and net income of US$2,906 million, and subsequently increased its quarterly dividend by US$0.07 to US$1.27 per share, payable on March 4, 2026, to shareholders of record on February 23, 2026. The sharp improvement in quarterly earnings alongside a higher dividend underscores how recent refining performance and cash generation are supporting more generous shareholder returns.
